bug.short_desc: CommandManager + CommandHandler to organize and suspend commands

long_desc.thetext:
Commands are acting in a global context. Some times you will be able to active commands with some keys for a circumscribed context. That's why we should offer command grouping and a registrar to active or rather suspend this groups.
For a quicker start up, I made a small app with a possible implementation, see attachment.
To be able to decide when an activated command should really enabled (there can be some reasons to be disabled, even after activation) I used a small "state machine". But for a more generic purpose we should (like Martin recommended) use a new property like "on" to suspend or activate commands without touching the enabled property.
One additional point is to suspend all commands automatically if any input field is focused. No one wont's to trigger an command on "Del" key has been pressed if you are in a text field.
